            <p class="text-[9px] text-[var(--color-text-faint)] mt-2">Bands: {(cluster.bands || []).join(', ')}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <!-- SECTION 5: MOLECULAR DEPENDENCY CHAIN                      -->
  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->

  <section class="mb-10 reveal">
    <h2 class="text-lg font-bold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] mb-1">Molecular Dependency Mapping</h2>
    <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-faint)] mb-6">QIF maps attacks from the hourglass band level down to molecular structure. This section demonstrates how a single pathway disruption cascades through biochemical dependencies.</p>

    <!-- Reward center attack example -->
    <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5 sm:p-8 mb-6 border-l-4 border-purple-500">
      <h3 class="text-base font-bold text-[var(--color-text-primary)] mb-2">Case Study: Reward Center Attack &mdash; Dopamine Dependency Chain</h3>
      <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-faint)] italic mb-4">For threat modeling purposes. Diagnostic category references, not diagnostic claims.</p>

      {mesolimbicPathway && (
        <div class="glass rounded-lg p-4 mb-5">
          <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 mb-2">
            <span class="text-xs font-mono px-2 py-0.5 rounded bg-purple-500/20 text-purple-400">{mesolimbicPathway.id}</span>
            <span class="text-sm font-semibold text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">{mesolimbicPathway.name}</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-2">{mesolimbicPathway.function}</p>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 text-[10px]">
            <span class="px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded glass">Origin: VTA ({mesolimbicPathway.origin_band})</span>
            <span class="px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded glass">Targets: NAc, Amygdala, Hippocampus ({(mesolimbicPathway.target_bands || []).join(', ')})</span>
            <span class="px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded glass text-cyan-400">NT: Dopamine</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      )}

      <!-- Dopamine Synthesis Dependency Chain -->
      <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-[var(--color-text-primary)] mb-3">Dopamine Synthesis: Molecular Dependency Chain</h4>
      <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-4">Each step in dopamine synthesis depends on specific enzymes, cofactors, and minerals. Disrupting any link breaks the chain.</p>

      <!-- Visual chain -->
      <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-1 min-w-max px-2">
          <!-- Step 1: Phenylalanine -->
          <div class="glass rounded-lg p-3 min-w-[140px] text-center border-t-2 border-blue-400">
            <p class="text-xs font-bold text-blue-400">Phenylalanine</p>
            <p class="text-[9px] text-[var(--color-text-faint)]">Essential amino acid</p>
            <p class="text-[9px] text-[var(--color-text-faint)]">(dietary intake)</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-0.5 shrink-0">
            <span class="text-[var(--color-text-faint)]">&rarr;</span>
            <span class="text-[8px] text-amber-400 text-center leading-tight">PAH<br/>+ BH4, Fe&sup2;&plus;</span>
          </div>

          <!-- Step 2: Tyrosine -->
          <div class="glass rounded-lg p-3 min-w-[140px] text-center border-t-2 border-cyan-400">
            <p class="text-xs font-bold text-cyan-400">Tyrosine</p>
            <p class="text-[9px] text-[var(--color-text-faint)]">Non-essential amino acid</p>
            <p class="text-[9px] text-[var(--color-text-faint)]">(also from diet)</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-0.5 shrink-0">
            <span class="text-[var(--color-text-faint)]">&rarr;</span>
            <span class="text-[8px] text-red-400 text-center leading-tight font-semibold">TH<br/>+ BH4, Fe&sup2;&plus;, O&sub2;</span>
          </div>

          <!-- Step 3: L-DOPA -->
          <div class="glass rounded-lg p-3 min-w-[140px] text-center border-t-2 border-amber-400">
            <p class="text-xs font-bold text-amber-400">L-DOPA</p>
            <p class="text-[9px] text-[var(--color-text-faint)]">Rate-limiting step</p>
            <p class="text-[9px] text-red-400 font-semibold">TH = bottleneck</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-0.5 shrink-0">
            <span class="text-[var(--color-text-faint)]">&rarr;</span>
            <span class="text-[8px] text-green-400 text-center leading-tight">AADC<br/>+ PLP (B6)</span>
          </div>

          <!-- Step 4: Dopamine -->
          <div class="glass rounded-lg p-3 min-w-[140px] text-center border-t-2 border-green-400 ring-1 ring-green-400/30">
            <p class="text-xs font-bold text-green-400">Dopamine</p>
            <p class="text-[9px] text-[var(--color-text-faint)]">Active neurotransmitter</p>
            <p class="text-[9px] text-[var(--color-text-faint)]">→ reward, motivation</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Cofactor dependency table -->
      <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-[var(--color-text-primary)] mb-3">Critical Cofactors &amp; Dependencies</h4>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
        <table class="w-full text-xs">
          <thead>
            <tr class="border-b border-[var(--color-border)]/30">
              <th class="text-left py-2 px-2 text-[var(--color-text-faint)] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-[10px]">Cofactor</th>
              <th class="text-left py-2 px-2 text-[var(--color-text-faint)] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-[10px]">Required By</th>
              <th class="text-left py-2 px-2 text-[var(--color-text-faint)] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-[10px]">Role</th>
              <th class="text-left py-2 px-2 text-[var(--color-text-faint)] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-[10px]">If Depleted</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">
            <tr class="border-b border-[var(--color-border)]/10">
              <td class="py-2 px-2 font-semibold text-red-400">Iron (Fe&sup2;&plus;)</td>
              <td class="py-2 px-2">Tyrosine Hydroxylase (TH)</td>
              <td class="py-2 px-2">TH is an iron-dependent monooxygenase. Fe&sup2;&plus; is coordinated by His331, His336, and Glu376 in a facial triad at the active site. Requirement is absolute &mdash; no other divalent metal substitutes.</td>
              <td class="py-2 px-2 text-red-400">Dopamine synthesis halts at tyrosine. TH cannot convert tyrosine to L-DOPA without iron.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-[var(--color-border)]/10">
              <td class="py-2 px-2 font-semibold text-amber-400">Tetrahydrobiopterin (BH4)</td>
              <td class="py-2 px-2">TH &amp; PAH</td>
              <td class="py-2 px-2">Electron donor cofactor. Regenerated by dihydrobiopterin reductase (DHBR). Required for both phenylalanine &rarr; tyrosine and tyrosine &rarr; L-DOPA.</td>
              <td class="py-2 px-2 text-amber-400">Both conversion steps fail. Hyperphenylalaninemia + dopamine depletion.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-[var(--color-border)]/10">
              <td class="py-2 px-2 font-semibold text-green-400">Pyridoxal Phosphate (PLP/B6)</td>
              <td class="py-2 px-2">AADC (Aromatic L-Amino Acid Decarboxylase)</td>
              <td class="py-2 px-2">PLP-dependent decarboxylase. Removes carboxyl group from L-DOPA to produce dopamine.</td>
              <td class="py-2 px-2 text-green-400">L-DOPA accumulates but cannot convert to dopamine. Also affects serotonin synthesis (same enzyme).</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-[var(--color-border)]/10">
              <td class="py-2 px-2 font-semibold text-cyan-400">Molecular Oxygen (O&sub2;)</td>
              <td class="py-2 px-2">TH (hydroxylation reaction)</td>
              <td class="py-2 px-2">TH is a monooxygenase &mdash; inserts one oxygen atom into tyrosine to produce L-DOPA.</td>
              <td class="py-2 px-2 text-cyan-400">Hypoxia impairs dopamine synthesis. Relevant to cerebrovascular BCI complications.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-2 px-2 font-semibold text-blue-400">Ferritin</td>
              <td class="py-2 px-2">Iron storage &amp; buffering</td>
              <td class="py-2 px-2">Ferritin <strong>stores</strong> iron (up to 4,500 Fe&sup3;&plus; atoms per molecule). Releases Fe&sup2;&plus; when needed. Does NOT "need" iron &mdash; it <em>provides</em> iron to TH.</td>
              <td class="py-2 px-2 text-blue-400">Low ferritin = low iron reserves = eventual TH inactivation. Serum ferritin &lt;30 ng/mL associated with restless legs syndrome (dopaminergic).</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <!-- QIF Attack Scenario -->
      <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-[var(--color-text-primary)] mb-3">QIF Attack Scenario: Reward Circuit Disruption</h4>
      <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-4">A TARA technique targeting the mesolimbic pathway at band N5 (Basal Ganglia) would cascade through these molecular dependencies:</p>

      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-3 mb-4">
        <div class="glass rounded-lg p-3 border-l-2 border-red-400">
          <p class="text-[10px] text-red-400 font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider mb-1">Layer 1: Signal</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">DBS or TMS disrupts VTA &rarr; NAc dopaminergic signaling at the electrical/magnetic level</p>
          <p class="text-[9px] text-[var(--color-text-faint)] mt-1">Band: N2 &rarr; N5</p>
        </div>
        <div class="glass rounded-lg p-3 border-l-2 border-amber-400">
          <p class="text-[10px] text-amber-400 font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider mb-1">Layer 2: Synaptic</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">Altered firing rate in VTA dopamine neurons changes vesicular dopamine release at NAc synapses</p>
          <p class="text-[9px] text-[var(--color-text-faint)] mt-1">Mechanism: frequency-dependent release</p>
        </div>
        <div class="glass rounded-lg p-3 border-l-2 border-purple-400">
          <p class="text-[10px] text-purple-400 font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider mb-1">Layer 3: Molecular</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">Sustained disruption alters TH phosphorylation (Ser40), changing enzyme activity. Chronic over-stimulation depletes BH4 and iron cofactors.</p>
          <p class="text-[9px] text-[var(--color-text-faint)] mt-1">Dependency: Fe&sup2;&plus; &rarr; TH &rarr; L-DOPA &rarr; DA</p>
        </div>
        <div class="glass rounded-lg p-3 border-l-2 border-cyan-400">
          <p class="text-[10px] text-cyan-400 font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider mb-1">Layer 4: Clinical</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">Anhedonia, motivational deficit, or reward hypersensitivity. Corresponds to DSM-5-TR diagnostic categories for depressive, substance use, or impulse control disorders.</p>
          <p class="text-[9px] text-[var(--color-text-faint)] mt-1">DSM refs: F32.x, F14.x, F63.0</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Iron-Ferritin direction clarification -->
      <div class="glass-subtle rounded-lg p-4 border-l-2 border-blue-400">
        <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-primary)] font-semibold mb-1">Clarification: Ferritin &harr; Iron Direction</p>
        <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">
          Ferritin does not "need" iron. The relationship is: <strong>Ferritin stores iron</strong> (as Fe&sup3;&plus;) and <strong>releases it</strong> (as Fe&sup2;&plus;) when enzymes like Tyrosine Hydroxylase require it. The correct dependency chain is:
        </p>
        <p class="text-xs font-mono text-[var(--color-accent-primary)] mt-2 text-center">
          Dietary iron &rarr; Transferrin (blood transport) &rarr; Transferrin receptor (neuronal uptake) &rarr; Ferritin (intracellular storage) &rarr; Fe&sup2;&plus; release &rarr; TH active site &rarr; Dopamine synthesis
        </p>
        <p class="text-[10px] text-[var(--color-text-faint)] mt-2">
          Sources: Daubner et al. (2011) "Tyrosine Hydroxylase and Regulation of Dopamine Synthesis" <a href="https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC3065393/" class="text-[var(--color-accent-primary)]">PMC3065393</a>;
          Matak et al. (2016) "Disrupted iron homeostasis causes dopaminergic neurodegeneration" <a href="https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC4822577/" class="text-[var(--color-accent-primary)]">PMC4822577</a>;
          Erikson et al. (2000) "Iron-restricted diet affects brain ferritin and dopamine metabolism" <a href="https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC5434142/" class="text-[var(--color-accent-primary)]">PMC5434142</a>;
          Kandel et al., Principles of Neural Science, 6th ed.; Stahl, Essential Psychopharmacology, 5th ed.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

